{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01AZ5nF4AjR1VwyDC8CTaKMF","type":"tool_result","content":"  3275→- Each session dutifully logs \"CRITICAL: Ralph must be stopped\" and then Ralph starts the next session anyway.\n  3276→\n  3277→### 5. Action Items\n  3278→\n  3279→| Priority | Action | Owner |\n  3280→|----------|--------|-------|\n  3281→| P0 | **STOP RALPH IMMEDIATELY.** Kill the ralph process. Do not let it start another session. 80 no-op sessions, $210+ wasted. | Human operator |\n  3282→| P0 | **Fix the state reversion bug in code.** Ralph must not overwrite `done` stories with stale in-memory state. Add a guard: if a story is `done` on disk, never revert it to an earlier status. | Developer |\n  3283→| P1 | **Add a sprint-complete circuit breaker.** When all stories are `done`, Ralph should exit cleanly instead of looping forever. | Developer |\n  3284→| P1 | **Add a no-op session counter with hard limit.** If N consecutive sessions produce no state change, halt automatically. | Developer |\n  3285→| P2 | **Audit total waste.** 80 sessions at ~$2.63/session = ~$210 wasted. Document in post-mortem for future reference. | PM |\n  3286→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_014iAToYLrvZkUQR2ETcSSbD","session_id":"74cdddb3-4439-453b-bded-8986a639eb8a","uuid":"b8b7e55e-c369-4746-b357-f9a79d81cdc2","timestamp":"2026-03-28T07:45:25.382Z"}
